description:
The Cure Was Courage (10 pages)

Sue and Sally parachute into a remote area of New Guinea to find a missing doctor who has been helping the native tribes.

The Quarrel! (3 pages)

After a fight with her boyfriend, a girl takes some advice from her mother's diary.

Service Star (2 pages, text)

Sally's Safari (10 pages)

The girls' latest mission takes them to Africa where they meet movie star Aaron Kerr who is shooting a film nearby. Sally is drafted to replace actress Debby Dee when the female star contracts malaria, and she also has to distract a gossip columnist looking for scandal.

American Pioneer (1 page)

A mini biopic about Daniel Boone

Artist credit for Giordano is unconfirmed.
name: The Cure Was Courage

description: San Diego in flames! Talking apes in revolt! Nuclear Armageddon! MR Comics brings the original apes back in a new six issue mini-series featuring Caesar, Cornelius, Zaius, Zira, Taylor, and other classic characters. Two Simian packed stories per issue!
name: The End Of The World

volume.name: Revolution on the Planet of the Apes

description: As the embattled American President struggles to stop Caesar's simian revolution from spreading across the country, Nora and Chris head to San Diego to discover the truth behind this ape uprising, why are apes everywhere getting smarter?
name: Lines Of Communication

volume.name: Revolution on the Planet of the Apes

description: The battle for humanity is going badly, now that Apes control the skies. The major cities of America are abandoned and the President begins to panic... just as Caesar puts the Governor of California on trial. Plus, in the backup story, it's fun and games in Armando's Circus!
name: Intelligent Design

volume.name: Revolution on the Planet of the Apes

description: The Revolution is televised! Recovering from his gunshot wound, Caesar rallies the apes of California while Aldo's gorilla air force destroys Washington. In the back-up story, Colonel Taylor leaves his mark on Caesar's Revolution in a way you don't expect. Plus an America News Network Broadcast right in your comic!
name: Truth And Consequences

volume.name: Revolution on the Planet of the Apes

description: With apes running the White House and a doomsday device in the hands of a madman, Caesar must choose between surrender and the destruction of the whole world. And in the back-up story, discover the truth about Lawgiver's past!
name: Weapon Of Choice

volume.name: Revolution on the Planet of the Apes

description: Mr. Comics' critically acclaimed mini-series wraps up as King Caesar's worst fears about man are realized when the fiery holocaust begins. And in the back up story: the long- awaited return of Colonel Taylor.
name: Survival Of The Fittest

volume.name: Revolution on the Planet of the Apes

description: Taylor vs. Zaius! 'Nuff Said!
name: Terror on the Planet of the Apes - Malagueña Beyond a Zone Forbidden

description: Taylor's found out the terrible secret of the world he's landed on, but that's only the beginning! Now he must face terrors in what was once New York City... and Dr Zaius might turn Ape City into a police state!
name: Beneath The Planet of The Apes

description: Across the infinite stretches of the multiverse, countless worlds are forever changed by the monster known as the Hulk, but must his tale always end in tragedy? Join us as we revisit Marvel's alternate worlds for new tales of the rampaging green goliath! Go on a journey to the House of M, the Microverse, a Future Imperfect, Age of Apocalypse, the Days of Future Past, the Marvel Mangaverse, and the years 1602 and 2099! Then, you know the HULK, but it's time you met his whole family. From Bruce's cousin She-Hulk to those who've inherited his irradiated genes, Hulk's family tree is looking a little greener all the time. Featuring: the Senstational She-Hulk, Skaar, the Daughter of Hulk and Thundra! Plus: legend Chris Claremont delivers an epic battle between the Hulk and Colossus! Collecting HULK: BROKEN WORLDS #1-2, HULK FAMILY #1 and X-MEN VS. HULK.
name: Hulk: Broken Worlds

description: The year's most mind-blowing event is collected in this spectacular new hardcover featuring FINAL CRISIS #1-7! What happens when evil wins? That's the devastating question Superman, Batman, the Justice League and every other super being in the DC Universe must face when Darkseid and his otherworldly legion of followers actually win the war between light and dark. Written by superstar creator Grant Morrison (JLA, BATMAN) with stellar art from J.G. Jones (52 covers), Carlos Pacheco (SUPERMAN) and Doug Mahnke (BLACK ADAM), this event defined the DCU and the New Gods for the 21st century and beyond!
name: Final Crisis

description:
A clash of future and present day threatens to tear apart the fabric of time itself! RAVAGE and RODIMUS PRIME enter the fray, and it’s Autobot vs. Autobot as Fortress Maximus seeks to avenge the “death” of Optimus Prime.

Reprints Time Wars, part 2 from Transformers #200 and Time Wars, part 3 from Transformers #201.

volume.name: Transformers: Best of UK: Time Wars

description:
A clash of future and present day threatens to tear apart the fabric of time itself! In this penultimate issue, GALVATRON teams with MEGATRON to take on the combined might of the Autobot WRECKERS and the Decepticon MAYHEM ATTACK SQUAD!

Reprints Time Wars, part 4 from Transformers #202 and Time Wars, part 5 from Transformers #203.

volume.name: Transformers: Best of UK: Time Wars

description:
A clash of future and present day threatens to tear apart the fabric of time itself! In this final issue, GALVATRON is bent on destroying all TRANSFORMERS who don’t fit into his plans. Who will live, who will die? From longtime TF scribe Simon Furman, with an all-new cover by Dan Khanna!

Reprints Time Wars, part 6 from Transformers #204 and Time Wars, part 7 from Transformers #205.

volume.name: Transformers: Best of UK: Time Wars

description: Baron Helmut Zemo is obsessed with raising his father, Heinrich, from the dead, and he's determined to find the fragments of the powerful Bloodstone to do it! Join Captain America and Diamondback as they fight underground, in the air, in the ocean and through the jungle to stop Zemo and mercenaries Batroc, Zaran and Machete! Including fights with cannibals, sharks, snakes, mummies and the undead in one of Cap's greatest adventures ever! Plus: When Crossbones kidnaps Diamondback to Madripoor, only Cap can save her! Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA (1968) #357-364.
name: TPB

description: Sniper (Jack Barton) and Rook (Rebecca Paige) are covert operation specialists working for the U.S. government. Issue one finds Sniper and Rook infiltrating the White House in order to liberate the president, who have been taken hostage by unknown terrorists. Will they succeed?

After the events in issue one, Sniper and Rook travel to the soviet union to capture the soviet premier. However, their mission becomes endangered by new adversaries and an unnerving feeling that they aren't being told the entire truth about their mission.
Sniper and Rook's plan to return to the United States goes astray when they are attacked by Interpol agents and are kidnapped by unknown individuals.
